[SN]TITLE[SN]
Four Cardiff men charged in slavery investigation

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Four men have been charged in an investigation into modern day slavery.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
All four are from the Rumney area of Cardiff and were arrested last June.
A 58-year-old man has been charged with two counts of kidnap and four of assault occasioning actual bodily harm (AOABH) ; a 38-year-old and a 33-year-old have been charged with one count of kidnap and a 35-year-old faces ones count of AOABH.
They will appear in Newport Magistrates' Court later this month.
Det Supt Paul Griffiths of Gwent Police said: "This is a welcome development for the Operation Imperial investigation, which has been in place investigating allegations of modern day slavery, forced labour and other offences over a period of 30 years."
